of Arts and Sciences.

00:04:23.100 --> 00:04:26.110
I first met Terrance
in Pittsburg, in 1994,

00:04:26.110 --> 00:04:29.030
which was almost half my life ago.

00:04:29.030 --> 00:04:33.070
I have seen him grow and mature
as a poet, editor and teacher

00:04:33.070 --> 00:04:37.320
in those years, but I've also
seen how constant he has been

00:04:37.320 --> 00:04:40.150
in his dedication to
poems and poets.

00:04:40.150 --> 00:04:41.920
How generous he is as a friend.

00:04:41.920 --> 00:04:48.260
And his poems have always seemed
super charged by a signature mix

00:04:48.260 --> 00:04:50.490
of invention and immediacy.

00:04:50.490 --> 00:04:54.110
Myth making and memory
contended; playful, riffing,

00:04:54.110 --> 00:05:01.240 position:56%
and exploding personas; arguments of
the subline and a whole [inaudible].

00:05:01.240 --> 00:05:05.280
He is as a lyricism of
life in [inaudible] though,

00:05:05.280 --> 00:05:10.000
and takes a maximal approach in
contrast to, or even bolstered

00:05:10.000 --> 00:05:13.540
by the rigor of its music.

00:05:13.540 --> 00:05:17.030
