00:06:57.110 --> 00:07:03.330
I want to start by
talking about your family.

00:07:03.330 --> 00:07:05.730
What kind of family raised you?

00:07:05.730 --> 00:07:12.760
&gt;&gt; TERRANCE HAYES: Well, my mother
had me when she was about 16.

00:07:12.760 --> 00:07:17.500
So, that meant we pretty
much grew up together.

00:07:17.500 --> 00:07:18.920
&gt;&gt; RON CHARLES: Just you?

00:07:18.920 --> 00:07:20.220
&gt;&gt; TERRANCE HAYES: Yeah,
well I have a brother.

00:07:20.220 --> 00:07:24.100
She met my stepdad
when I was about 4.

00:07:24.100 --> 00:07:29.580
So, he's been there and has
been there for a long time.

00:07:29.580 --> 00:07:31.760
And he was a pretty creative dude.

00:07:31.760 --> 00:07:33.150
He was in the military.

00:07:33.150 --> 00:07:37.140
So, for many years we moved
and then eventually we sort

00:07:37.140 --> 00:07:38.920
of stopped and he kept going.

00:07:38.920 --> 00:07:42.970
But, he's retired now
and he's actually

00:07:42.970 --> 00:07:44.960
in a new job working
as a prison guard.

00:07:44.960 --> 00:07:46.260
Which is what my mother did.

00:07:46.260 --> 00:07:53.050
She talked him into becoming a
prison guard after he retired

00:07:53.050 --> 00:07:58.420
from the military,
and then she retired.

00:07:58.420 --> 00:08:02.950
But yeah so they're you
know good, regular people.

00:08:02.950 --> 00:08:08.500
When people ask me about their
influence what I say is they just

00:08:08.500 --> 00:08:10.250
never discouraged me
which was great.

00:08:10.250 --> 00:08:14.430
So, that they were curious and
they thought I was curious.

00:08:14.430 --> 00:08:18.640
But no one ever said, don't
go to your room and write.

00:08:18.640 --> 00:08:24.350
They did say, you know, why are
you always reading those books,

00:08:24.350 --> 00:08:25.650
