00:12:18.460 --> 00:12:19.760
&gt;&gt; TERRANCE HAYES: Yeah.

00:12:19.760 --> 00:12:21.060
&gt;&gt; RON CHARLES: It's just?

00:12:21.060 --> 00:12:22.360
&gt;&gt; TERRANCE HAYES: A cousin of
mine, who also probably of all

00:12:22.360 --> 00:12:23.660
of my family, my first cousin,

00:12:23.660 --> 00:12:24.960
Pervis [assumed spelling] is
a person who's most interested

00:12:24.960 --> 00:12:26.260
in my work.

00:12:26.260 --> 00:12:27.810
He also is a prison guard.

00:12:27.810 --> 00:12:33.130
But he said about het "Late"
poem, because he remembered it

00:12:33.130 --> 00:12:34.920
because I went and
stayed with his mother.

00:12:34.920 --> 00:12:36.220
&gt;&gt; RON CHARLES: After this ordeal.

00:12:36.220 --> 00:12:37.520
&gt;&gt; TERRANCE HAYES: His
mother is my mother's sister.

00:12:37.520 --> 00:12:39.000
Yeah, and he was like come on man.

00:12:39.000 --> 00:12:40.970
You did not say, oh I'm a son.

00:12:40.970 --> 00:12:43.920
You were so mad you wanted to
have her arrested [laugther].

00:12:43.920 --> 00:12:46.180
And to him I said, yeah,
but that's not interesting

00:12:46.180 --> 00:12:47.480
for the poem though, you know.

00:12:47.480 --> 00:12:52.440
So, he had a better sense of
both the real-time response to it

00:12:52.440 --> 00:12:55.730
and the sense of like
calling me on it in fact.

00:12:55.730 --> 00:12:58.760
But I was like yeah, but you
know there has to be a turn.

00:12:58.760 --> 00:13:00.210
So, and I said but that was better.

